 data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Correct_Century\" title=\"Correct Century\">Correct Century</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 105 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Correct Century&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Correct+Century\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li><a href=\"/wiki/Cosmic_Era\" title=\"Cosmic Era\">Cosmic Era</a> <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 993 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;Cosmic Era&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=Cosmic+Era\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li><li>K\u014dreki <span class=\"plainlinks\" title=\"Search the other 10 pages containing the property &quot;Era&quot; with the value &quot;K\u014dreki&quot;\"><span class=\"mw-default-size\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"https://gundam.fandom.com/wiki/Special:SearchByProperty?property=Era&amp;value=K%C5%8Dreki\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\"><img alt=\"Icon - Search\" src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAIABAAAAAP///yH5BAEAAAEALAAAAAABAAEAQAICTAEAOw%3D%3D\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"12\" height=\"12\" class=\"mw-file-element lazyload\" data-image-name=\"Icon - Search.png\" data-image-key=\"Icon_-_Search.png\" data-relevant=\"0\" data-src=\"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/gundam/images/e/ef/Icon_-_Search.png/revision/latest?cb=20120427204701\" /></a></span></span></li></ul></div>\n</div>\n</aside>\n\n</p><p><b>High Grade Universal Century (HGUC)</b><span style=\"font-weight: normal\"> (<span class=\"t_nihongo_kanji\" lang=\"ja\">\u30cf\u30a4\u30b0\u30ec\u30fc\u30c9 \u30e6\u30cb\u30d0\u30fc\u30b5\u30eb\u30bb\u30f3\u30c1\u30e5\u30ea\u30fc</span><span class=\"t_nihongo_comma\" style=\"display:none\">,</span> <i><span class=\"t_nihongo_romaji\">Hai Gur\u0113do Yunib\u0101saru Senchur\u012b</span></i><span class=\"t_nihongo_help\"><sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Help:Japanese\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Help:Japanese\"><span class=\"t_nihongo_icon\" style=\"color:#00e;font:bold 80% sans-serif;text-decoration:none;padding:0 .1em;\">?</span></a></sup></span>)</span> is a line of 1/144 scale&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Gunpla\" title=\"Gunpla\">Gunpla</a> model kits of the <a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suits\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mobile Suits\">Mobile Suits</a> from the <a href=\"/wiki/Universal_Century\" title=\"Universal Century\">Universal Century</a> timeline of the <i>Gundam</i> meta series. First produced in 1999, the line is a successor to the original <a href=\"/wiki/High_Grade_(1990)\" title=\"High Grade (1990)\">High Grade</a> line. The line inherited many of the improvements of its predecessor, such as snap-fit assembly, while further improving the detail, color separation, and articulation of kits.\n</p><p>In 2009, the HGUC line incorporated the sub-line <a href=\"/wiki/Universal_Century_Hard_Graph#High_Grade_U.C._Hard_Graph\" title=\"Universal Century Hard Graph\">High Grade U.C. Hard Graph</a>, which featured kits with 1/144 scale military vehicles and soldiers in addition to Mobile Suits.\n</p><p>Starting in 2010, the line also extended to the <a href=\"/wiki/After_Colony\" title=\"After Colony\">After Colony</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/After_War\" title=\"After War\">After War</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Future_Century\" title=\"Future Century\">Future Century</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Cosmic_Era\" title=\"Cosmic Era\">Cosmic Era</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Correct_Century\" title=\"Correct Century\">Correct Century</a> timelines with the HGAC, HGAW, HGFC, HGCE, and HGCC lines, respectively, as part of what was later dubbed the \"HG All Gundam Project\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>1<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup> The alternate timeline kits are distinguished by a silver stripe on the front of the box, as opposed to the gold stripe featured on HGUC kits, as well as a corresponding variation of the HG logo.\n</p><p>In 2015, Bandai announced the \"Revive\" project to celebrate the 35th anniversary of Gunpla.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>2<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup> Starting with the <a href=\"/wiki/RX-77-2_Guncannon\" title=\"RX-77-2 Guncannon\">RX-77-2 Guncannon</a>, previous HGUC releases are given a complete redesign using newer technology with further improved detail and articulation, alongside modernized proportions.\n</p><p>To prepare for the 40th anniversary of Gunpla in 2020, the \"Gunpla Evolution Project\" began in 2017.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\"><span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#91;</span>3<span class=\"cite-bracket\">&#93;</span></a></sup> Showcasing improvements/innovations in specific areas, this project involved Gunpla from multiple lines, with the first kit released being a redesign of the <a href=\"/wiki/MSZ-006_Zeta_Gundam\" title=\"MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam\">MSZ-006 Zeta Gundam</a>.\n</p><p>Following the reorganization of Bandai Namco Group, box covers of reissue and future release of kits from September 2018 onwards feature a blue Bandai logo instead of the original red logo, while releases and reissues from mid-2022 onwards further feature the Bandai Namco logo on the upper right corner.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Regulars_and_Special_Editions\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Regulars and Special Editions</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Exclusives\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Exclusives</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Trivia\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Trivia</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">6</span> <span class=\"toctext\"