e=\"MS-06S Zaku II Commander Type\">Char's Zaku II</a> was a recolor of the&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/High_Grade_Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_The_08th_MS_Team\" title=\"High Grade Mobile Suit Gundam: The 08th MS Team\">HG08</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/MS-06JC_Zaku_II\" title=\"MS-06JC Zaku II\">MS-06JC Zaku II</a> kit (which was previously released as a JAF-CON exclusive set with the clear version of the <a href=\"/wiki/RX-79%EF%BC%BBG%EF%BC%BD_Gundam_Ground_Type\" title=\"RX-79\uff3bG\uff3d Gundam Ground Type\">RX-79[G] Gundam Ground Type</a>) made for the U.S. market in 2001 before the new mold was released in 2002.</li>\n<li>Shorter Mobile Suits, such as those from the late Universal Century and After Colony timelines are often not actually designed in 1/144 scale; instead being 1/132 scale.</li>\n<li>Though <i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam_SEED_Freedom\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Freedom\">Mobile Suit Gundam SEED Freedom</a></i> kits are part of the High Grade Cosmic Era sub-line, they use a different typeface for the mobile suit name and model number.</li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Mobile_Suit_Gundam:_Requiem_for_Vengeance\" title=\"Mobile Suit Gundam: Requiem for Vengeance\">Mobile Suit Gundam: Requiem for Vengeance</a></i> kits are not listed on the boxart as being part of the Universal Century, but do include the gold accenting reserved for Universal Century kits.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a title=\"Sign in to edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" data-tracking-label=\"log-in-edit-section\" data-action=\"edit-section\" href=\"https://auth.fandom.com/signin?redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fgundam.fandom.com%2Fwiki%2FHigh_Grade_Universal_Century%3Fveaction%3Dedit%26section%3D4&amp;uselang=en&amp;metadata=article-registration-edit-article-section\" data-testid=\"log-in-edit-section\" aria-label=\"Sign in to edit\"><svg class=\"wds-icon wds-icon-ti